'''Augustine Boakye''' (born 3 November 2000) is a Ghanaian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{French football updater|Saint-Étienne}} club [[AS Saint-Étienne|Saint-Étienne]] and the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]].

==Career==
Boakye began his football career with [[West African Football Academy|WAFA]] in the [[Ghana Premier League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/talent-tavern-wafa-whiz-kid-augustine-boakye-marks-ghana-premier-league-debut-in-liberty-win |title=Talent Tavern: WAFA whiz kid Augustine Boakye marks Ghana Premier League debut in Liberty win |date=27 March 2018 |accessdate=12 April 2020 |publisher=Ghana Web}}</ref>

In August 2021, Boakye signed a four-year contract with [[Austrian Football Bundesliga]] club [[Wolfsberger AC]].<ref name="rzp">{{cite web |title=Servus Augustine {{!}} RZ Pellets WAC |url=https://www.rzpelletswac.at/2021/08/31/servus-augustine/ |website=Wolfsberger AC |language=de-DE |date=31 August 2021}}</ref>

In July 2024, Boakye joined [[Ligue 1]] side [[AS Saint-Étienne|Saint-Étienne]], signing a four-year deal with an option of an additional year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.asse.fr/fr/actualites/augustine-boakye-est-vert--ac36879|title=Augustine Boakye est Vert !|publisher=[[AS Saint-Étienne]]|date=13 July 2024|accessdate=15 July 2024}}</ref>

